{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #30: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $h(N)$ be the maximum size of a Sidon set in $\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$. Is it true that, for every $\\epsilon>0$,\\[h(N) = N^{1/2}+O_\\epsilon(N^\\epsilon)?\\] Current best: Erd\\H{o}s and Tur\\'{a}n \\cite{ErTu41} proved an upper bound of $N^{1/2}+O(N^{1/4})$, with an alternative proof by Lindstr\\\"{o}m \\cite{Li69}. The current record is\\[h(N)\\leq N^{1/2}+0.98183N^{1/4}+O(1),\\]due to Carter, Hunter, and O'Bryant \\cite{CHO25}. and Roy, S., An upper bound on the size of Sidon sets. Prize: $1000. OEIS: A003022, A143824, A227590. Tags: additive combinatorics, number theory, sidon sets.","id":"vf_e670784f00284ad6","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos30.erdos_30 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos30.erdos_30.","id":"vf_f5547ac404a7ff5c","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"attempted via frontier 'sidon/B2' (transfer_strength=partial) -> no_progress","claimed_status":"draft","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_428fa3a012df9043","kind":"dead_end","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"sidon/B2","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_428fa3a012df9043","trust":"signed"},{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"OEIS A309370 (max Sidon subset of {0,1}^n) a(23) >= 5179: an independently verified Sidon set of 5179 points in {0,1}^23 (all 13413610 pairwise componentwise sums distinct), extending the sequence to n=23 where no value was recorded. Built by lifting the best n=22 set (3770) into {0,1}^23 and greedily adding new-coordinate vectors; re-checked from scratch by an independent pairwise-sum-distinctness verifier.","claimed_status":"verified_computationally","classif